 engine/tests/slice10_node_validity.rs:624) must be rewritten, not deleted — they were the drift guard and must be replaced by an INTEGER equivalent. LAYERING CALL OWED TO THE HITL: storage and the governed SDK surface should both become INTEGER, but the BYO-LLM EXTRACTOR JSON should KEEP ISO-8601 with engine-side normalisation on ingest — an LLM cannot reliably emit epoch seconds, and that boundary already has a normalisation layer. This is a layering boundary, not splitting the difference on the representation; flagging it explicitly because it is adjacent enough to the direction call that the HITL should confirm it. MIGRATION MECHANICS: SQLite has no ALTER COLUMN TYPE, and the pinning test asserts declared type == TEXT, so true harmonisation requires a 12-step TABLE REBUILD of canonical_edges (create-new / copy-with-conversion / drop / rename), not an UPDATE in place. HAZARD: strftime('%s', x) returns NULL on an unparseable value, and a NULL t_invalid READS AS 'still valid' — so a junk value silently RESURRECTS an invalidated edge. That must be a RED test and a migration-time hard failure, never a silent NULL. SCHEDULING NOTE: this needs schema step 24 (23 being the EAV/registry step), making FOUR migrations in 0.8.20. I-6 'one migration per release' is GUIDANCE, not enforced — there is no test counting steps per release, and 0.8.20 already ships two (21 and 22), which dev/plans/0.8.6-0.8.16-PROGRAM-SEQUENCING.md:417 explicitly blesses. So four is precedented but should be surfaced, not slipped through."}
